<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
There has always been a great deal of confusion about the type; see, e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Hitchcock, AS" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the United States National Herbarium" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="113 - 158" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/13772page/148/mode/1up" refId="B29" refString="Hitchcock, AS, 1908. Types of American grasses: A study of the American species of grasses described by Linnaeus, Gronovius, Sloan, Swartz and Michaux. Contributions from the United States National Herbarium 12 (3): 113 - 158, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/13772page/148/mode/1up" title="Types of American grasses: A study of the American species of grasses described by Linnaeus, Gronovius, Sloan, Swartz and Michaux." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/13772page/148/mode/1up" volume="12" year="1908">Hitchcock (1908)</bibRefCitation>
or 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/2423880" author="Gould, FW" journalOrPublisher="American Midland Naturalist" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="36 - 59" refId="B26" refString="Gould, FW, Ali, MA, Fairbrothers, DE, 1972. A revision of Echinochloa in the United States. American Midland Naturalist 87 (1): 36 - 59, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/2423880" title="A revision of Echinochloa in the United States." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/2423880" volume="87" year="1972">Gould et al. (1972)</bibRefCitation>
. In fact, all original material came from North America and belongs to 
<taxonomicName family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. muricata" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="muricata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. muricata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; in 1753 
<taxonomicName family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. crus-galli" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="crus-galli">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. crus-galli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from Eurasia, was not yet a widespread introduced species in North America. 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.12299" author="Crespo, MB" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="820 - 822" refId="B18" refString="Crespo, MB, Martinez-Azorin, M, Angeles Alonso, M, Pena-Martin, C, 2020b. Proposal to conserve the name Panicum crus-galli (Echinochloa crus-galli) (Poaceae, Panicoideae) with a conserved type. Taxon 69 (4): 820 - 822, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.12299" title="Proposal to conserve the name Panicum crus-galli (Echinochloa crus-galli) (Poaceae, Panicoideae) with a conserved type." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.12299" volume="69" year="2020 b">Crespo et al. (2020b)</bibRefCitation>
formally proposed to conserve the binomial 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. crus-galli" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="crus-galli">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. crus-galli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a conserved type based on the specimen Herb. Burser I: 103 (UPS), the one previously chosen as 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“lectotype”">&quot;lectotype&quot;</normalizedToken>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Michael, PW" journalOrPublisher="Canadian Journal of Plant Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B50" refString="Michael, PW, 1983. Taxonomy and distribution of Echinochloa species with special reference to their occurrence as weeds of rice. In: International Rice Research Institute (IRRI) and International Weed Science Society (Org.) Proceedings of the Conference on Weed Control in Rice, 31 August-4 September 1981. International Rice Research Institute, Manila, 291-306." title="Taxonomy and distribution of Echinochloa species with special reference to their occurrence as weeds of rice. In: International Rice Research Institute (IRRI) and International Weed Science Society (Org.) Proceedings of the Conference on Weed Control in Rice, 31 August- 4 September 1981. International Rice Research Institute, Manila, 291 - 306." year="1983">Michael (1983)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
